works.complaint:
The URLS and domain names contain and use the YONJA  
trademark (as registered in Turkey and USA) in a way that attempts to trade  
off the goodwill embodied in the Yonja Trademark and in a way that would  
cause consumer confusion about the source of the content. Moreover, the  
content also poses Trademark Dilution, and due to it's adult nature,  
Trademark Tarnishment threats as well.

The content, most blatantly the "siberyonja.com" site, also likely violates  
the Anticybersquatting Consumer Protection Act (“ACPA”), which makes it  
illegal to register an Internet domain name that consists of another's  
distinctive trademark for purposes of commercial gain.
